.TH "arm_iommu_attach_device" 9 "arm_iommu_attach_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
arm_iommu_attach_device \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" arm_iommu_attach_device
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct dma_iommu_mapping *mapping "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
valid struct device pointer
.IP "mapping" 12
io address space mapping structure (returned from
arm_iommu_create_mapping)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Attaches specified io address space mapping to the provided device.
This replaces the dma operations (dma_map_ops pointer) with the
IOMMU aware version.

More than one client might be attached to the same io address space
mapping.
